 Removing the Hack-Tools Extension
Opened Firefox.

Typed about:addons in the address bar and pressed Enter.

In the Extensions tab, located the extension named Hack-Tools.

Clicked on the three-dot menu (⋯) next to Hack-Tools.

Selected "Remove" from the dropdown options.

Confirmed the removal when prompted.

✅ Reason for Removal:
Not actively used in regular browsing.

Requests access to private windows and restricted sites, which poses potential privacy risks.

Better to keep the browser clean with only necessary extensions to minimize attack surface.
